<TITLE> Six 'razakars' sued in C'ganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainawabganj, Apr 13 (bdnews24.com)  A war crimes case was filed against six individuals who collaborated with the Pakistan army during the Liberation War of 1971. The charges were brought on Tuesday in Chapainawabganj for murder of freedom fighters. Rahima Begum, wife of a martyred freedom fighter, filed the case with the Chief Judicial Magistrate's court of Basudeb Roy. The judge, taking the case into cognisance, ordered the police to take legal action after investigation. The accused in this case are Nazrul Islam, 60, Saidur Rahman, 80, Fazlur Rahman, 85, Kaifur Rahman alias Luka, 75, Bishu, 80, and Nazrul Islam alias Fuka, 80. All of them are residents of Rehaichar area of the city. The case says that the six 'razakars' took away Gias Uddin, a freedom fighter and also the husband of the plaintiff, from his home on Sep 15, 1971. Later, they gunned him down beside the Mahananda river, the statement added. bdn
